parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden loss of engine power can cause the vehicle to stall or lose propulsion, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when transporting sensitive passengers such as school children.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses propulsion
the vehicle is unable to maintain speed
the vehicle is unable to accelerate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fire originating from the right front heater fan can spread rapidly, engulfing the vehicle and posing a significant risk to the safety of passengers, particularly those with mobility impairments.
symptoms: Smoke coming from the heater fan
heavy smoke pouring from the heater vent
flames visible inside and outside the windshield
